nter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... --> |postal_code = |area_code = |blank1_name = [[Köppen climate classification|Climate]] |blank1_info = [[Tropical savanna climate|Aw]] |website = {{URL|alcaldialibertador-carabobo.gob.ve}} |footnotes = }} '''Tocuyito''' is a city of [[Venezuela]], capital of the [[Libertador Municipality, Carabobo|Libertador Municipality]] in [[Carabobo State]]. It is part of the metropolitan area of [[Valencia (Venezuela)|Valencia]]. This city is considered the entry point to Valencia from the motorways that lead to the Southwest (Barquisimeto) and South (towards Cojedes).
==Geography== Tocuyito is located in the flatlands of Carabobo, at an altitude of 451 metres above sea level. Its annual temperature is around 26[[°C]].
==History== Tocuyito was founded in 1547 by Spanish Conquistador Juan de Villegas. The name derives from its initial similarity to the town of [[El Tocuyo]] (Tocuyito is little Tocuyo). '''Tocuyo''' is an Indian word for "[[maniok]] juice".
There was an important battle in Tocuyito on 14 September 1899, when the so-called Revolution for Liberal Restoration, led by [[Cipriano Castro]], decisively defeated the governmental forces of president [[Ignacio Andrade]].
